            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a small bowl with a splash of <strong>boiling water</strong> and stir until the salt has dissolved</p><p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and your <strong>dried cranberries </strong>and set aside to pickle – these are your<strong> quick-pickled cranberries</strong></p><p>Cut a piece of<strong> tin foil</strong>, then trim and add your <strong>green beans</strong> to the middle with a splash <strong>cold water </strong>and scrunch the edges together to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
