            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, cut the <strong>sage</strong> <strong>stuffing</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces and drain the <strong>quick-pickled cranberries</strong></p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Return the<strong> shredded chicken</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: If the gravy hasn't thickened, increase the heat to high and cook for a few min further!</p>",
